<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  ChannelMe! - channel editor dialog (1920x1080 design space; Kodi scales).
  Three columns: category sidebar (100) | content panel | Save(900)/Cancel(901).
  Control IDs are referenced from resources/lib/editor.py - keep them in sync.

  Panel visibility -> Container(100).CurrentItem. All label TEXT is set from Python
  (storage.L); the English here is a harmless fallback.

  CURSOR vs SELECTION (important):
    * A Kodi list draws its focusedlayout for its current item even when the list
      is NOT focused. To avoid a phantom bright cursor on panels you haven't
      entered, the bright cursor (button_focus) is gated on Control.HasFocus(<list>).
    * SELECTION is ambient: a row with Property(sel)=1 (or an 'on' filter) shows a
      deep-blue bar FF0E597E (darker than the cursor). Filters: deep-blue on, field
      colour off, bright on focus. Surfaces are blue-tinted hex; named colours
      (button_focus/white/grey) track the active skin. white.png tinted.
-->
<window type="dialog">
  <defaultcontrol always="true">100</defaultcontrol>
  <controls>

    <!-- ================= Frame ================= -->
    <control type="image">
      <left>0</left><top>0</top><width>1920</width><height>1080</height>
